# Theme & Color System Rules

## CRITICAL: Uniform Color Usage

**ALWAYS use the defined color system below. NEVER create custom color combinations or deviate from this palette.**

---

## Primary Color Palette

### Brand Colors

**ALWAYS use these exact colors for brand elements:**

```typescript
// Primary Brand Colors
blue-500    // Primary actions, main CTAs, links
blue-600    // Primary hover states, active states
blue-700    // Primary pressed states, emphasis

indigo-500  // Secondary actions, accents
indigo-600  // Secondary hover states
indigo-700  // Secondary pressed states

purple-500  // Tertiary actions, optional fields
purple-600  // Tertiary hover states
purple-700  // Tertiary pressed states
```

### Semantic Colors

**ALWAYS use these for semantic meanings:**

```typescript
// Success
green-500   // Success messages, completed states
green-600   // Success hover states

// Warning
yellow-500  // Warning messages, caution states
yellow-600  // Warning hover states

// Error/Destructive
red-500     // Error messages, destructive actions
red-600     // Error hover states, destructive hover

// Info
blue-500    // Info messages (same as primary)
blue-600    // Info hover states
```

