## Text Colors

### Primary Text

**ALWAYS use semantic text colors:**

```typescript
// Primary text (body, headings)
className="text-foreground"           // Uses CSS variable
className="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100"

// Secondary text (descriptions, hints)
className="text-muted-foreground"     // Uses CSS variable
className="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400"

// Muted text (subtle, disabled)
className="text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-500"
```

### Gradient Text

**For emphasis and headings, use gradient text:**

```typescript
// Primary gradient (most common)
className="text-transparent bg-clip-text bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-600 to-purple-600"

// Alternative gradient
className="text-transparent bg-clip-text bg-gradient-to-r from-indigo-600 to-purple-600"
```

**DO NOT use:**
- ❌ Solid colors for headings (use gradients instead)
- ❌ Different gradient directions
- ❌ More than 2 colors in a gradient

